name: TagTransparency
shortdesc: Options for specifying how tranparencies are displayed.

property.name: OFF
property.shortdesc: Turns off the on-screen display of transparency. Note: Does not turn off transparency when printing or exporting the file.

property.name: LOW_QUALITY
property.shortdesc: Displays basic transparency &#40;opacity and blend modes) and shows transparency effects such as drop shadow and feathering in a low-resolution approximation. Note: Does not isolate page content from the background. Objects with blend modes other than Normal might appear different in other applications and output.

property.name: MEDIUM_QUALITY
property.shortdesc: Displays drop shadows and feathering in low resolution.

property.name: HIGH_QUALITY
property.shortdesc: Displays higher-resolution &#40;144 dpi) drop shadows and feathers, CMYK mattes, and spread isolation.

property.name: DEFAULT_VALUE
property.shortdesc: Uses the default setting. For information, see display performance preferences.
